Description: Fragment of oval handle of a pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay near fine orange-buff; some mica. Rectangular stamp. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 122, 2? The three signs appear in a different order on Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, Fou.03.10973.8 (Senol 2016 186, no. 44), suggesting that the 'phi' is a symbol accompanying a name, Ni----- ; the stamp is not close to the examples from the Serce Limani wreck published by Grace and cited there.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1593)
